[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Gradle dependencies**\n\nI’m looking into a Gradle dependency conflict where two artifacts contain the same classes. This could lead to duplicates on the classpath. If both are included, I wonder if the classpath order affects which classes are targeted. For testing API metadata, adding an implementation dependency might include unnecessary classes and mess with coverage. Existing tests cover part of this, but I need to decide if extra dependencies are appropriate for meaningful test coverage. Should I keep it simple or am I missing something?\n\n**Inspecting old version coverage**\n\nI'm thinking about the existing coverage from an old version that dealt with CommandInfo$Beans and SecuritySupport resources. It didn't seem to rely on the com.sun package. For version 1.2.1, I'm curious if the javax package includes anything from com.sun. It looks like I need to inspect the old POM and JAR files to get a clearer picture. This should help me determine what dependencies and resources are actually necessary.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02b547b1915350e0016a41afa3051081959bee8fceea0a27bc\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQa-svpmDOI1RNhb-l3lLx9YyVCWALMHTN7A4uOEP08pCZQyKxTMJIzr73PgfLbs7VVA-S_hgrl1GBHcD9Yk2qVgGnPjvhkZFeZcnfYcTTwd9ocrIF_9hDYS6Wo6ladsitA-f2Bhza_x0aop5YOCMMhANkIhan5YBzWybauvZcaMr0qZWAK5h56jzDjopSQ9Z2ft6Z-cNtBze3X8Um05flcr2fTkag4Qym8sZdShjGjXcP-o7hX6JK_-sUDfGdeW1lJeFh8OxiSxAIcQnVyUYCUjgpCxR6naIbbW2kLP3lu3r-5cGJH4QSA2YN6eUHnOxZPPQs-m14KgmpZAsWqgl7jwhrgQoVrwXPvnNzQtJAcQCqmnyW0FGuV62nbByzzQCgENZOj5evSlNLQ0R0mvl4bOgqyWh_CDQ8BWW1rvAed5K4KPflgsfCNEL4NhUgIXgK1fisemYsHIrdk3EZhJyQPf-FX8rIy93me3qhbOdV_e0jbDrjeQls0z3G2qFXvdKp4eEerctxvqXzNB1sOzrWr-M9YIalR_tAGHPRqQMYhwmQbmU5TkfoytXehmWUtzitFH8p5tH0gpzmvOs60wy7Vs6s7f7zTiG9j5tGWh6Lcn4jHYFPK7mQ7uhSjmNqpAIUFVW6pRm47Bd9vsJCD8fvMSBdC2rAEXMN8cNSiiPNyQpEIKRG71MOue2_ULt6